	the properties relevant for the amplification process: surface density,
	thermal stability towards thermocycling, functionalization reproducibility
	and storage stability. The derivatization process, first developed
	for glass slides, was then adapted to microfabricated glass channels
	containing integrated fluidic connections. This implementation resulted
	in an important reduction of reaction times, consumption of reagents
